      "writtenOn": "2016-01-11T19:24:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "tl;dr\n- I\u0027ll name this ParallelTask\n- I _may_ re-implement async based on this object (I ask for your opinion below).\n- I\u0027ll provide a async(...).then(...) API based on this object.\n\n------------\nIt does indeed implement future-\u003ethen, but...\n\n- I don\u0027t like the term \"async\" used to mean \"parallel\". An async task can run in parallel or not (three options: launch a thread, post to an existing event loop, defer computation to point of first use). In this case, I necessarily want parallel execution, since the intention is to do blocking IO.\n\n- Going with the OOP interface we have for android::base::Thread, I do want to create a similar object here.\n\n- As for async(), I was first going to rewrite async to use this instead. \n  - I _really_ don\u0027t like Thrad::onExit. ;-)\n  - But, in it\u0027s current implementation, async() can be used without a running event loop, but not this object. This object necessarily needs the event loop, since that\u0027s where the \u0027then\u0027 part is posted.\n  - How do you feel about the async--\u003elooper dependence?",
      "parentUuid": "6a901bcb_440922b5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 59,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 59,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "bd2b98db63897d03ed2252bffdaae87a4997b6a7",
